1.6 Planned changes to improve safety

The primary mechanisms to identify and plan safety improvements include (but are not limited to):

 - Process Hazard Analysis Update;
 - Cal/ARP Seismic Assessment;
 - Compliance Audits;
 - Mechanical Integrity Program (Routine Inspections & Maintenance);
 - IIAR Bulletin 109 Inspections; 
 - WPS Inspection Protocol; and,
 - WPS Food Safety Program

The programs above may result in recommendations ranging from capital improvements to routine maintenance. Where appropriate service calls are established in parallel to identified needs. Current planned changes to improve safety include recommendations as a result of the Process Hazard Analysis (PHA) performed May 16, 2019. The local Fire Department/CUPA was invited to participate and did attend the PHA.  Recommendations have been compiled; reviewed by management, and a written implementation schedule has been prepared. A summary includes maintenance items and administrative improvements. The completion of 2019 PHA recommendations is scheduled by 12/31/2019.  

End of Executive Sum
